:::s22:::Several years go by , until one night a familiar figure barges into Pip 's room -- the convict , Magwitch , who stuns Pip by announcing that he , not Miss Havisham , is the source of Pip 's fortune .
:::s24:::Pip is appalled , but he feels morally bound to help Magwitch escape London , as the convict is pursued both by the police and by Compeyson , his former partner in crime .
:::s25:::A complicated mystery begins to fall into place when Pip discovers that Compeyson was the man who abandoned Miss Havisham at the altar and that Estella is Magwitch 's daughter .
p :::s34:::The time comes for Pip and his friends to spirit Magwitch away from London .
p :::s37:::Pip and Herbert hurry back to effect Magwitch 's escape .
:::s40:::Magwitch is sentenced to death , and Pip loses his fortune .
